**Table of Contents**

1. # **Introduction**

   1. # **Purpose**

This *Software Requirements Specification and Design Document* describes the software requirements and system design for the development of the **IELTS Practice Website Integrated with AI**, built using **React** for the frontend and **Express.js** for the backend.

The purpose of this document is to provide a comprehensive description of the system’s functionality, architecture, and design specifications to guide the development, testing, and deployment of the web application. It ensures that all project stakeholders — including developers, testers, and users — have a shared understanding of the system’s goals, behavior, and design approach.

The document defines both the functional and non-functional requirements of the system, along with technical specifications for AI integration that enables **automatic Speaking and Writing evaluation** and **simple feedback generation**.

2. # **Scope**

The **IELTS Practice Website Integrated with AI** is an online platform designed to assist learners in preparing for the IELTS exam. The system provides users with tools to practice **Writing, and Speaking** sections.

The key features of the application include:

* AI-based **automatic scoring and feedback** for Speaking and Writing tasks.  
* A user-friendly **practice interface** with question banks, mock tests, and progress tracking.  
* A **secure authentication system** for both learners and administrators.  
* A **dashboard** to review user performance and suggest areas for improvement.

The system aims to make IELTS preparation more accessible and effective by combining modern web technologies and artificial intelligence to simulate a realistic test experience.

3. # **Intended Audiences and Document Organization**

This document is primarily intended for the following audiences:

* **Development Team:**  
   Responsible for implementing system functionalities based on the specified requirements and design.  
* **QA/QC Team:**  
   Responsible for reviewing requirements, verifying design completeness, and ensuring overall software quality through the testing lifecycle.  
* **Tester Team:**  
   Responsible for designing and executing test cases, conducting functional and non-functional tests, and validating that all requirements are met.

Additionally, this document may serve as a reference for **project supervisors or instructors** to review the project’s progress and compliance with software engineering standards.

Below are main sections of the document:

* **1\. Introduction**: This section describes the general introduction of this document.

* **2\. Functional Requirements**: This section describes the functional requirements in detail.

* **3\. Non-functional Requirements:** This section describes the non-functional requirements of this application such as user access and security, interfaces, screens and performance.

* **4\. Other Requirements:** This section describes other requirements such as archive or security audit function.

* **5\. UI/UX Requirement:** This section describes the design of the application.

* **6\. Appendixes**: This section describes other requirements for this application and other supporting information for this document**.**

* NOTE: Please refer to section 6.1 for all acronyms and abbreviations you may encounter within this document.

2. # **Functional Requirements**

   1. # **Use Case Description**

### UC1: Sign Up

| Name |  Sign Up (Account Registration) |
| :---- | :---- |
| **Description** | This use case enables a **Guest** to create a **Learner** account, receive an e-mail verification link, and if configured automatically signed in after successful verification. |
| **Actor** | Guest (Unauthenticated user) |
| **Trigger** | The Guest clicks **“Create Account / Sign Up”** after entering valid **{e-mail, password, display name}**. Or The Guest selects **“Sign Up with Google”** (or another OAuth provider) and the platform receives a valid identity token. |
| **Pre-condition** | The user is not currently authenticated. The e-mail address does **not** already exist in the **User** table. |
| **Post-condition** | A new **User** record is created with status **PendingVerify**. *(If the “auto-login after sign-up” flag is enabled)* the system issues a **JWT/Session** and redirects the user to the **Dashboard**. |

#### **Activities Flow**

![][image1]

*Figure 1: Activities Flow*

#### **Business Requirements**

| Activity | BR Code | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| ***(2)*** | ***BR1*** | **Required Fields:** The Sign-Up form must contain \[Email\], \[Password\], and \[Display Name\]. The "Submit" button remains disabled until all fields are filled. |
| ***(4)*** | ***BR2*** | **Email Format:** The \[Email\] must follow the standard RFC 5322 format. It must not contain spaces. Max length: 255 characters. If invalid → Show **MSG-001**. |
| ***(4)*** | ***BR3*** | **Email Uniqueness:** The system checks if the \[Email\] already exists in the database (case-insensitive). If exists → Show **MSG-002**.	 |
| ***(4)*** | ***BR4*** | **Password Complexity:** Password must be between 8 and 32 characters long. It must contain at least: 1 Uppercase letter, 1 Lowercase letter, 1 Number, and 1 Special character. If not → Show **MSG-003.** |
| ***(4.2)*** | ***BR5*** | **Success Action:** Upon successful registration, create a new User record with status `PendingVerify`."→ Show **MSG-004.** |

### UC2: Sign In

| Name |  Sign In |
| :---- | :---- |
| **Description** | This use case lets a registered **Learner** (or **Admin**) authenticate, obtain a valid session/JWT, and reach their intended page (Dashboard by default). |
| **Actor** |   Learner (primary), Admin (secondary) |
| **Trigger** | The user clicks **“Sign In / Login”** after entering **{e-mail, password}**. |
| **Pre-condition** | The user is currently unauthenticated. A **User** record with status **Verified** exists for the e-mail provided. The account is **Active**. |
| **Post-condition** |  A JWT / Session cookie is issued and stored.  A LoginSuccess audit/event record is written {userId, ip, userAgent, ts}. The user is redirected to their last intended URL or /dashboard. |

#### 

#### **Activities Flow**

![][image2]

#### **Business Requirements**

| Activity | BR Code | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| ***(4)*** | ***BR6*** | **Credential Validation:** Verify if \[Email\] exists and \[Password\] hash matches. If mismatch → Show **MSG-005**. |
| ***(4)*** | ***BR7*** | **Status Check:** The account must have status `Active` and `Verified`. If locked or unverified → Show **MSG-006**. |
| ***(4.2)*** | ***BR8*** | **Lockout Policy:** If the user enters the wrong password **5 consecutive times** within 10 minutes, lock the account for 15 minutes and show **MSG-007**. |

### UC26: Retake Practice

| Name | Retake Practice |
| :---- | :---- |
| **Description** | Allows the learner to redo a previous practice prompt without overwriting the original attempt. |
| **Actor** | Learner |
| **Trigger** | The learner clicks **"Retake"** on a completed attempt or prompt. |
| **Pre-condition** | The original prompt still exists in the system.  The learner is authenticated. |
| **Post-condition** | A new attempt is created for the same prompt.  Original attempt remains unchanged. |

#### **Activities Flow**

![][image26]

#### **Business Requirements**

| Activity | BR Code | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| ***(3)*** | ***BR63*** | **Prompt Availability:** If the prompt has been deleted or disabled, show **MSG-031** and prevent retake. |
| ***(5)*** | ***BR63*** | **New Attempt:** Create a new AttemptID linked to the same PromptID. Previous attempts remain accessible. |

### UC27: Log Out

| Name | Log Out |
| :---- | :---- |
| **Description** | Allows an authenticated user to securely log out of the system, invalidating their session. |
| **Actor** | Learner, Teacher |
| **Trigger** | The user clicks **"Log Out"** from the menu or profile dropdown. |
| **Pre-condition** | The user is currently authenticated with a valid session. |
| **Post-condition** | JWT/Session token is invalidated. The user is redirected to the login page. Local storage is cleared. |

#### **Activities Flow**

![][image27]

#### **Business Requirements**

| Activity | BR Code | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| ***(2)*** | ***BR64*** | **Confirmation:** No confirmation dialog required for logout (single-click action). |
| ***(4)*** | ***BR65*** | **Token Invalidation:** The server must invalidate the JWT/refresh token to prevent reuse. |
| ***(5)*** | ***BR66*** | **Clear Storage:** Clear all sensitive data from local storage and session storage. |

Security Rules:

* **Authentication:** All API endpoints (except Login/Register) must require a valid JWT (JSON Web Token).  
* **Encryption:** User passwords must be hashed using **Bcrypt** before storing in the database.  
* **Data Transmission:** All data transfer between Client and Server must be encrypted via **HTTPS (TLS 1.2+)**.  
* **Input Validation:** All user inputs (forms, file uploads) must be sanitized to prevent SQL Injection and XSS attacks.
